pr_title: [FEAT]: CCV Parser & Ingestion of CCV into database
pr_body:
This pull request covers the parser which converts the CCV xml files into a key, value nested structure. This structure has been ingested to the database. The parser can be executed by using the following command ```bash python3 manage.py parse_ccv sample_ccv/ccv_sample_2.xml ```
Main logic of the parser and ingestion is in parse_ccv.py file.

pr_title: Test Cases for Parser & Sample files for the deployment
pr_body:
This PR covers the test cases for the parser which invokes the parses sample ccv xm file and test the ingested data from models.
The tests can be invoked by using `tox` command in the root directory
```bash
tox -e pytest
```

This also contains the sample files for the deployment.

pr_body:
This PR covers the endpoint for listing the ccvs and it's relevant data.

1. Endpoint to return the available ccvs

```
http://127.0.0.1:8000/ccv
```

This also contains the unit test case for the same.
